The World Governing Council of Airports Council International (ACI) has appointed Capt. Rabiu Yadudu, Managing Director of Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) as its member.
Mrs Henrietta Yakubu, the General Manager, Corporate Affairs, FAAN, said this in a statement on Thursday in Lagos.
Yakubu said Yadudu was appointed alongside two others- Mr Emanuel Chavez of Aeroportos de Mozambique (president) and Mr Dewananda Chellen of Airports of Mauritius Co. Ltd (member)Â  as African representatives on the board.
The appointment took immediate effect.

